What's in my Nightime Skincare Routine? ✨🎑🌜

My skin type: Oily to combination + slight acne prone

Nightime Skincare is the game changer 👏 TRUST ME! It heals the skin from within as the products get a good amount of time (7-8hrs) to do their job 😍 without any environmental changes. 

You can actually see the difference when you wake up ✨ 

Here are the products I use in Nigh Skincare Routine in the following order:

🌜 Face wash (Daily): @biodermaindia Pigmentbio foaming cream or the @neutrogena.india Oil-free Acne wash
 rinse or the @lotus_herbals Apricot Scrub
🌜 Retinol or Azelaic Acid serum (Daily - Either mix together or alternate): @medidermapro_col Retises 1% serum,  @sesdermaindia Azelac RU serum
🌜 Moisturizer (Daily): @belifindia True Cream Aqua Bomb or the @clinique_in Dramatically Different Moisturizing Gel
🌜 Sleeping mask for hydration (2-3x a week): @belifindia Aqua Bomb Sleeping mask , @laneigeindia Water Sleeping mask 
🌜 Lip balm (Daily): @flpindia Aloe Lips
I give a gap for about a min between each step in order to give time for the product to get absorbed in the skin!

‼️Note: Please do not use Retinol or Azelaic acid if you are pregnant or breastfeeding‼️

I follow this religiously everyday & it has worked wonders for my skin *touchwood*

REMEMBER, SKINCARE TAKES TIME! DON'T EXPECT ANY PRODUCT TO SHOW RESULTS IN A WEEK OR TWO. 

GIVE IT ATLEAST 3 MONTHS OF CONSISTENT USAGE TO DECIDE IF THIS PRODUCT WORKS FOR YOU OR NOT! 🌟

Happy skincare :)

How to gain healthy weight during pregnancy? 🤰🥦

Pregnant women need only about 300 healthy calories a day than they did before they were pregnant. This will help them gain the right amount of weight during pregnancy. 

On the occasion of International Day of Action of Women's Heath on Saturday, 28 May 2022, catch me  in conversation with Dr. Eileen Canday, Head, Nutrition & Dietetics of the Sir H. N. Reliance Foundation Hospital and Research Centre @rfhospital to understand how to gain healthy weight during pregnancy. 

Dr. Eileen Canday specializes in several areas such as Critical care, Oncology, Renal Nutrition, Bariatric nutrition, Weight loss and Nutrigenetic. She is a Diabetes Educator having completed professional qualifications from International Diabetes Federation and is a member of the Association of Diabetes Educators.

What's in my Daytime Skincare Routine? ☀️✨🤩

My skin type: Oily to combination + slight acne prone

A decade back, my skin was full of pimples, acne and red marks. It was as if you could not see the skin below 😬😜 My pimples also sometimes had puss (so yeah it was really bad)

In 2011, I started reading about skincare and visited a dermatologist. That's when I started realising the imp of taking care of skin esp in my 20s in order to have a good skin for life. ♥️

And from then to now, you can see the difference! 🤩 

But mind you, all this is a result of consistent skincare & a good diet! ✨

Here are the products I use in Daytime Skincare Routine in the following order:

☀️ Face wash (Daily): @biodermaindia Pigmentbio foaming cream or the @neutrogena.india Oil-free Acne wash
☀️ Scrub or exfolate (2-3x a week): @nathabit.in 5 gram face mura & jojoba rinse or the @lotus_herbals Apricot Scrub
☀️ Toner (2-3x a week): @clinique_in No. 3 Clarifying Lotion or the @paulaschoice 2% BHA liquid exfoliant
☀️ Vit-C serum (Daily): @sesdermaindia C-Vit serum or the CEEMOCEE Vit-C serum
☀️ Moisturizer (Daily): @belifindia True Cream Aqua Bomb or the @clinique_in Dramatically Different Moisturizing Gel
☀️ Sunscreen (Daily): @bioreindia UV Watery Essence SPF 50+ or the @thebodyshopindia Skin Defence SPF 50+

I give a gap for about a min between each step in order to give time for the product to get absorbed in the skin!

I also follow this religiously everyday!! 😎

REMEMBER, SKINCARE TAKES TIME! DON'T EXPECT ANY PRODUCT TO SHOW RESULTS IN A WEEK OR TWO. 

GIVE IT ATLEAST 3 MONTHS OF CONSISTENT USAGE TO DECIDE IF THIS PRODUCT WORKS FOR YOU OR NOT! 🌟

Happy skincare :)

Welcome to #EpisodeZ of my A–Z Kids Series 💙 where every letter leads to 🧮 learning, parenting hacks & lots of food 🍒

Z: Zero Prep Sandwich 🥪 Ideas for Busy Tiffin Mornings

These zero prep sandwiches have saved me more times than I can count! Because some days… we don’t have time, but nutrition can’t wait!

🥕Hummus Carrot Sandwich – Just spread hummus, add grated carrots along with a dash of salt pepper Classic Hummus @wingreensfarms 
🥑Avocado Sandwich – Mash a ripened avocado with a pinch of salt & pepper add finely chopped onion & tomato 
🍓Strawberry Chia Sandwich – Just spread jam + sprinkle some chia seeds. Strawberry Jam @our.littlejoys (Code: Tanya10*)
🥜🍌Peanut Butter Banana Sandwich – Slice banana, add peanut butter. Unsweetened Peanut Butter @banter.kitchen (Code:Tan10)
🌽Cheese Corn Sandwich – Mix boiled corn with grated cheese and add salt, pepper, mixed herbs as per taste. Grated mozzarella cheese @amul_india 
🍞The Real French Toast – Whisk an egg, add some milk, 1/2 tbsp jaggery powder, 1/4 tsp vanilla essence & a dash of cinnamon. Dip bread, toast it. 
🍫Chocolate Spirals – Just spread the chocolate spread over bread & sprinkle it with crushed almond powder. Chocolate Spread @our.littlejoys (Code: Tanya10*)
🥚Egg Sandwich – Whisk 1 egg, add salt & pepper as per your taster, 1/2 finely chopped onion & tomato. Add some butter or ghee to a non-stick pan, pour the egg mixture onto the pan, spreading it slightly. Quickly place a slice of bread over the raw egg mixture in the pan, gently pressing it down so it sticks to the egg.

Try these this week & tell me your child’s fav!

*valid on orders above 799

Welcome to #EpisodeX of my A–Z Kids Series 💙 where every letter leads to 🧮 learning, parenting hacks & lots of food 🍒

X: Xtra Curricular Activities ideas for preschoolers 

My 5 year old goes for swimming , skating, art, kathak, gymnastics, storytelling, tennis post school and people often ask me 🤔— Tanya, isn’t it too much? How does she manage? Doesn’t it get tiring?

And here’s what I have to say—
👉She likes all of these classes and happily looks forward to each of them post school. I have never pressurised or forced her to go
👉I want her to be exposed to different forms of art, sports, dance, music in her prime early years for her to develop an interest early on and pursue them as a passion along with her studies - and maybe even professionally later on
👉As a single working mom and Noor being a single child, I want her to be engaged in meaningful activities post school, rather than just wasting time around helps.
And fyi - She does get her slot for outdoor park playtime and even free-play time post dinner
👉Going for these classes also gets her in a proper routine and makes her exhausted enough for the day to eat and sleep well
👉She meets different people, kids and teachers at different classes which has made her very social and confident in communication 

So I don’t think it’s overloading. It’s just age-appropriate exploring! Because these early years are golden—& I want her to shine in every space she enters !

Also, we do each of these classes just twice or thrice a week!
